<HEADLINE>
NEW FSC HEAD TAKES OFFICE
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan. 30 (CNA) 01/30/07  21:18:10 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Tsai Ing-wen praised new Financial Supervisory
Commission (FSC) Chairman Hu Sheng-cheng's professionalism
Tuesday, describing Hu as "competent" for the top financial
supervisor post.
</P>
<P>
Tsai made the remarks while speaking at a changeover ceremony
during which Hu succeeded Shih Jun-ji as FSC chairman. Shih
tendered his resignation Jan. 12 to assume political
responsibility for the run on the Chinese Bank earlier this month
and the financial fiasco of the bank's parent company, the Rebar
Asia Pacific Group.
</P>
<P>
Hu served as chairman of the Council for Economic Planning and
Development (CEPD) and minister without portfolio before assuming
his current post, Tsai said, adding that he was in charge of
reviewing various financial bills and regulations governing the
establishment of the FSC while working as minister without
portfolio.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Hu promised to step up financial reforms.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day,  Minister-without-Portfolio Ho Mei-yueh
succeeded Hu as CEPD head. Ho once served as CEPD vice chairwoman
and economics minister.
</P>
